# Crown-Gold / pmppm-com — H5 SPA + Next.js root CSP snippet.
#
# Why this exists / why it's weaker than cg-csp-login.conf:
#   The login page (cg-csp-login.conf) is a 480-line hand-rolled HTML with
#   exactly one inline <style> + one inline <script>, no eval, no dynamic
#   resource fetching from third-party origins, and no user-content
#   rendering. That made `default-src 'none'` + tight allowlists feasible.
#
#   The Next.js SPA (/h5/sports.html and the pmppm.com root) emits the
#   React Server Components hydration payload via many inline <script>
#   tags like:
#       <script>self.__next_f.push([1, "....."])</script>
#   These are produced by Next.js's static export and rebuilt on every
#   `npm run build` with chunk-content-dependent hashes. We can't use
#   hash-based script-src (5+ hashes per page, change every build) and
#   we can't use nonces (static export = no per-request backend to inject
#   them; nginx sub_filter would have to rewrite every <script> tag).
#
#   So the pragmatic CSP for the SPA: 'unsafe-inline' for script and
#   style (kills CSP's primary XSS defence), but every OTHER directive
#   is locked down. In particular:
#     - object-src 'none'        kills Flash/legacy plugin XSS
#     - base-uri 'self'          stops <base href=evil.com>
#     - form-action 'self'       stops cred POST to evil.com
#     - frame-ancestors 'none'   kills clickjacking
#     - connect-src 'self' wss:* allows fetch + WebSocket to same-origin
#                                (we deliberately allow wss:* schemewide
#                                because /api/external/ws is sibling-of-
#                                Cloudflare and edge IP may vary)
#     - upgrade-insecure-requests  forces any stray http:// to https
#
# Third-party origins we allow:
#   - https://media.api-sports.io
#       Source of league / team / country crest PNGs.  The backend stores
#       only the relative path (e.g. "football/leagues/169.png") and the
#       list view renders `<img src="https://media.api-sports.io/...">`
#       directly.  Without this on img-src the list shows broken-image
#       icons for every league header.
#   - https://static.cloudflareinsights.com
#       Cloudflare Web Analytics beacon (auto-injected by CF when the
#       zone has Web Analytics enabled).  Needed on script-src to load
#       beacon.min.js and on connect-src for its sendBeacon POST.
#       Without these two we get a steady stream of CSP-violation noise
#       in every visitor's console even though no real feature breaks.
#
# Install path on server: /etc/nginx/snippets/cg-csp-spa.conf
add_header Content-Security-Policy "default-src 'self'; script-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline' https://static.cloudflareinsights.com; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'; img-src 'self' data: blob: https://media.api-sports.io; font-src 'self' data:; connect-src 'self' https://pmppm.com wss://pmppm.com wss: https://static.cloudflareinsights.com; worker-src 'self' blob:; manifest-src 'self'; object-src 'none'; base-uri 'self'; form-action 'self'; frame-ancestors 'none'; upgrade-insecure-requests" always;
